headline: Republic Services (RSG): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Over the last six months, Republic Services’s shares have sunk to $219.76, producing a disappointing 6.7% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 8.4% gain. This was partly driven by its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
